<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--CityHallCrash     07-17 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--City Hall Crash,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Drives Car Into City Hall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKE CHARLES, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman hit the gas pedal instead of the
brakes and drove through a plate-glass window into City Hall,
causing up to $30,000 in damage, the mayor said.
   ``We're lucky it was Sunday and not Monday,'' said Mayor Jim
Sudduth, noting that an employee usually sits next to the window the
car went through.
   The vehicle broke two tall window panes, an air conditioner, an
internal wall partition and water lines and knocked down a computer
and printer, said Sudduth.
   The 84-year-old woman, whom officials refused to identify, was
treated at St. Patrick Hospital and released.
   Sudduth said the woman veered the wrong way onto a one-way street
to avoid hitting a car ahead of her about noon Sunday.
   ``She thought she put her foot on the brakes, but she put it on
the accelerator,'' he said.
 
</TEXT>
