<SECOND>PM-Fire Deaths,0187</SECOND>
<HEAD>Six Die in Akron House Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An early-morning house fire killed six people
today, including a young mother and her three children, authorities
said.
   Three people escaped from the burning three-story home in a
moderate-income neighborhood, including a mother and daughter who
climbed out a second-story window and down a fire escape, the Fire
Department said.
   Five people were pronounced dead at the scene of the 1:30 a.m.
blaze, and an infant died at a hospital.
   Three firefighters suffered minor injuries, the Fire Department
said.
   Coroner's investigator Pat Gillespie identified the dead as Jerry
Jennings, 49, owner of the house; Jamie Scott, 22; Lynn Scott, 21,
and her children, Terrance, 3; Derrick, 18 months, and Brandon, two
weeks old.
   The relationships among all the victims were not immediately
known.
   Jackie Jennings and her daughter, Tyisha, escaped, as did Jerry
Jennings' wife, Mary, Gillespie said.
   The cause of the fire, which started on the first floor and
destroyed the home, was not immediately known. The blaze was spotted
by a police officer on patrol.
