<HEAD>11 Drowned or Missing in Rains</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Heavy rain in central and southern
provinces killed five people and left six others missing, the
National Disaster Center reported Monday.
   The weekend flooding also left 1,413 people homeless in six
provinces south of Seoul. The refugees were taken to schools and
churches and given food and clothing.
   Property loss, including damage to crops, was estimated at $4.2
million.
   Hardest hit was Taejon, 85 miles south of Seoul, where two
villagers drowned and another was missing when the area was battered
by 9.6 inches of rain Sunday, the government said.
   Service on the Kyongbu Railroad linking Seoul and Pusan was
disrupted for five hours Sunday when part of the line through Taejon
was submerged, according to the newspaper Dong-A Ilbo.
   The disaster center said 6,000 emergency workers and 50 pieces of
equipment were sent to the areas.
