<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Iran-Stamp     07-17 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Iran-Stamp,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Iran Issues First Stamps Picturing Khomeini</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran has issued its first two postage
stamps depicting Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini, it was reported Monday.
   Khomeini, who died June 3, had decreed that during his lifetime,
no pictures of him should appear on stamps or banknotes.
   A 20-rial (about 27-cent) stamp shows Khomeini ``smiling
contentedly as masses beneath mourn his death with a banner pledging
they would continue his path,'' the Islamic Republic News Agency
said.
   A 70-rial (about 94-cent) stamp is a portrait of Khomeini looking
down from a balcony, in his white robe and black cap, as he did
during audiences at his residence in north Tehran.
   The agency said there were no immediate plans to put Khomeini on
banknotes.
</TEXT>
