<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Soviet-Storm     07-17 0059</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Soviet-Storm,0060</SECOND>
<HEAD>Downed Power Line Kills Three in Gorky</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A storm struck the Gorky region and three people
were electrocuted by a downed power line, Tass said Monday.
   Hurricane-force winds smashed windows, tore roofs from buildings
and battered crops in the region 200 miles east of Moscow on Sunday,
the official Soviet news agency said.
</TEXT>
