<HEAD>Mating Ants Cover Lawns Like a Carpet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WICHITA FALLS, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It's mating season for red ants, and
residents of some neighborhoods are plagued with swarms so thick
their yards look like crawling red carpets.
   The swarms occur in the area every year as the ants mate, said
Randy Nash, a private exterminator.
   City and private exterminators spent the weekend blasting the
pests with sprays, and the problem is so bad it sent one woman to
the hospital.
   Evelyn Hoseid rushed from her ant-covered house for relief from
the swarms, and was overcome with effects of emphysema because she
forgot her oxygen tank. She was treated at Bethania Regional Health
Care Center and returned home to find piles of dead ants in the wake
of exterminators.
