<FIRST>r a AM-FBISoftball     07-17 0205</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-FBI Softball,0211</SECOND>
<HEAD>Agents Watch Local Police Arrest Their Man</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WESTERVILLE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thirty FBI agents having breakfast
before a softball tournament watched local police arrest a man the
agency had been seeking.
   Policeman J. Beachler said the agents watched from windows of
Cockerell's Restaurant as police arrested John R. Howard, 27, on a
charge of fleeing Pinellas County, Fla. The FBI said the suspect's
real name is Earn Howard.
   Police in this Columbus suburb said Howard is wanted in Florida
on child abuse and sexual assault charges involving a 13-year-old
girl. He was being held in the Franklin County Jail.
   Beachler said the FBI tracked Howard to the area. He was working
as a roofer.
   ``He was contacted by a local FBI agent posing as a builder, and
a meeting was arranged at the restaurant,'' Beachler said.
   ``It was purely accidental that the guys were in there for the
softball tournament,'' said Douglass Ogden, FBI senior agent in the
Columbus office.
   Westerville was host Saturday to the annual FBI Law Enforcement
Softball Tournament.
   FBI agent Doug Ogden said Monday that the Columbus FBI won the
unofficial softball tourney, but but he wouldn't say how many teams
played or how teams were elimated.
</TEXT>
