<HEAD>Soldiers Fire On Student Demonstration, Several Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soldiers opened fire on a
student demonstration Monday and at least five people, including an
American, were injured, witnesses and a Red Cross worker reported.
   Soldiers began firing after about 30 people gathered on the
campus of the University of El Salvador to protest the arrest of a
student leader, students said, speaking with the condition they not
b identified.
   They said the soldiers were trying to keep the demonstrators from
leaving the campus.
   A Red Cross worker said ambulances picked up several wounded
victims.
   Five people, including the American, were being treated at the
Rosales Hospital for injuries.
   The American identified himself to an Associated Press
photographer as Robert Drennuon, 33, of New York City. Drennuon said
he broke his leg running from the shooting.
