<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Closing,0153</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices hovered in a narrow range today as
the market's July rally flattened out.
   While the market gained ground in each of the first nine sessions
of July through the end of last week, the debate intensified over
when the advance might be due for at least a brief pause.
   But analysts said that mood of skepticism actually served to keep
the rally going for a while, by keeping the flow of potential buying
power into stocks at a slow but steady pace.
   Brokers said the new week began with an added element over
caution over the impending monthly report Tuesday on the nation's
international balance of trade.
   The data for May are expected to show an increase in the trade
deficit to $9 billion or more from $8.3 billion in April.
