<FIRST>u f AM-OilPrices     07-17 0182</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Oil Prices,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oil Prices Rise on Technical Factors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oil and gasoline futures prices advanced Monday
on largely technical factors.
   The August contract for West Texas Intermediate oil, the
benchmark grade of U.S. crude, picked up 13 cents to close at $20.45
a barrel in New York Mercantile Exchange trading. On Friday, the
contract fell 3 cents.
   Home heating oil rose 1.10 cent to close at 50.43 cents a gallon
after falling 0.11 cent on Friday, and wholesale unleaded gasoline
rose 0.24 cent to settle at 57.08 cents a gallon after slipping 0.62
cent on Friday.
   Richard Kane, a trader with Merrill Lynch Energy Futures, said
technical factors were largely the moving force Monday. Trading was
light, he said.
   In the gasoline market, some traders were squaring their
positions in advance of Tuesday's scheduled release of oil and gas
inventory figures by the American Petroleum Institute.
   In the crude market, Kane said there was more interest in
September and subsequent contracts _ which were up about 44 cents _
as the August contract is nearing its expiration.
</TEXT>
